name: Dr. Sarah Chen
bio: I specialize in helping professionals overcome burnout and work-related stress. With over 10 years of experience, I use evidence-based approaches including CBT and mindfulness techniques to help clients restore work-life balance and find meaning in their careers.

name: Dr. Michael Rodriguez
bio: I work with individuals experiencing anxiety disorders, panic attacks, and phobias. My therapeutic approach combines exposure therapy, cognitive restructuring, and relaxation techniques to help clients manage their anxiety and regain control of their lives.

name: Dr. Emily Thompson
bio: I specialize in trauma-informed care, helping survivors of trauma, PTSD, and complex trauma heal and rebuild their lives. I use EMDR, somatic experiencing, and narrative therapy to support clients in processing traumatic experiences safely.

name: Dr. James Wilson
bio: I focus on couples therapy and relationship counseling, helping partners improve communication, resolve conflicts, and strengthen their bond. I use Gottman Method, Emotionally Focused Therapy, and solution-focused approaches tailored to each couple's unique needs.

name: Dr. Lisa Park
bio: I specialize in treating depression, mood disorders, and helping clients navigate life transitions. My approach integrates interpersonal therapy, behavioral activation, and psychodynamic techniques to address both symptoms and underlying patterns.

name: Dr. Robert Martinez
bio: I work with adults and adolescents with ADHD, helping them develop executive functioning skills, time management strategies, and coping mechanisms. I combine cognitive-behavioral therapy with practical skill-building to support clients in achieving their goals.

name: Dr. Amanda Foster
bio: I specialize in grief counseling and loss, supporting individuals through bereavement, anticipatory grief, and complicated grief. I use person-centered therapy, meaning-making approaches, and expressive arts to help clients process their loss and find a path forward.

name: Dr. David Kim
bio: I focus on sleep disorders, insomnia, and helping clients develop healthy sleep hygiene. I use CBT for insomnia (CBT-I), relaxation training, and behavioral interventions to help clients achieve restful sleep and improve their overall well-being.

name: Dr. Jennifer Walsh
bio: I specialize in treating eating disorders including anorexia, bulimia, and binge eating disorder. With a compassionate and evidence-based approach, I help clients develop healthy relationships with food and their bodies using CBT-E, DBT, and family-based treatment methods.

name: Dr. Marcus Johnson
bio: I work with individuals struggling with substance use disorders and addiction. My practice focuses on harm reduction, relapse prevention, and recovery support. I integrate motivational interviewing, CBT, and 12-step facilitation to help clients achieve and maintain sobriety.

name: Dr. Priya Patel
bio: I specialize in LGBTQ+ affirmative therapy, providing a safe and supportive space for individuals exploring identity, coming out, or navigating relationship and family challenges. I use person-centered and narrative therapy approaches to honor each client's unique journey.

name: Dr. Thomas Anderson
bio: I focus on obsessive-compulsive disorder (OCD) and related anxiety conditions. I specialize in Exposure and Response Prevention (ERP) therapy, the gold standard treatment for OCD, helping clients break free from intrusive thoughts and compulsive behaviors.

name: Dr. Rachel Green
bio: I specialize in family therapy and working with children and adolescents. I help families improve communication, resolve conflicts, and navigate developmental challenges. I use structural family therapy, play therapy, and attachment-based interventions tailored to each family's needs.

name: Dr. Christopher Lee
bio: I work with individuals managing bipolar disorder and other mood disorders. My approach combines psychoeducation, mood tracking, medication adherence support, and cognitive-behavioral techniques to help clients stabilize their moods and build fulfilling lives.

name: Dr. Maria Santos
bio: I specialize in helping individuals with chronic pain and illness manage their physical and emotional well-being. I use acceptance and commitment therapy (ACT), mindfulness-based stress reduction, and pain psychology techniques to improve quality of life despite health challenges.

name: Dr. Kevin Brown
bio: I focus on men's mental health, addressing unique challenges men face including emotional expression, relationship difficulties, and societal expectations. I create a non-judgmental space where men can explore vulnerability, improve communication, and develop healthier coping strategies.

name: Dr. Nicole Taylor
bio: I specialize in postpartum depression and perinatal mental health, supporting mothers through pregnancy, birth, and early parenthood. I use interpersonal therapy, cognitive-behavioral techniques, and support groups to help women navigate this transformative life stage.

name: Dr. Daniel White
bio: I work with individuals struggling with social anxiety and shyness, helping them build confidence and develop social skills. I use exposure therapy, social skills training, and cognitive restructuring to help clients overcome fear of social situations and build meaningful connections.

name: Dr. Sophia Martinez
bio: I specialize in self-esteem and body image issues, helping clients develop self-compassion and positive self-concept. I integrate cognitive-behavioral therapy, self-compassion practices, and body-positive approaches to support clients in building healthier relationships with themselves.

name: Dr. Andrew Clark
bio: I focus on anger management and emotional regulation, helping individuals understand and manage intense emotions constructively. I use dialectical behavior therapy (DBT), mindfulness techniques, and cognitive restructuring to help clients respond to triggers more effectively.

name: Dr. Jessica Nguyen
bio: I specialize in working with immigrants, refugees, and individuals navigating cultural identity and acculturation challenges. I provide culturally sensitive therapy that honors clients' backgrounds while helping them navigate the complexities of living between cultures.

name: Dr. Ryan Mitchell
bio: I work with individuals experiencing career transitions, job loss, or professional identity crises. I help clients explore their values, skills, and passions to make informed career decisions and navigate workplace challenges with confidence and clarity.

name: Dr. Lauren Davis
bio: I specialize in personality disorders, particularly borderline personality disorder (BPD). I use dialectical behavior therapy (DBT) to help clients develop emotion regulation skills, improve relationships, and build a life worth living. I provide both individual and group DBT services.

name: Dr. Benjamin Harris
bio: I focus on helping individuals with perfectionism and high-functioning anxiety. Many of my clients are successful professionals who struggle with self-criticism, overthinking, and difficulty relaxing. I use CBT, ACT, and mindfulness to help them find balance and self-acceptance.
